Digital Accelerators

Operations Readiness

A well-architected Cloud Foundation sets the organization on an accelerated path to Digital

Every application to be hosted in Cloud relies on foundational services such as networking, identity & access management, data protection, etc. That is where a Cloud Foundation for enterprise-wide use comes into play.

Architecture

Future proof architecture that is highly resilient, secure, and scales with the organizations needs

Foundation to support growth and innovation

Security

Controls to meet regulatory requirements and industry standards (CIS, NIST CSF, PCI-DSS, HIPAA, etc.)

A secure and compliant cloud environment

Governance

Guardrails, policies, quotas, and budgets for cloud governance

Balancing user autonomy & centralized control

Automation

Infrastructure as code & reference pipelines for continuous application delivery

Self-service & automation for better developer experience

Visibility

Seamless integration of Cloud services and complimenting 3rd party tools

Better visibility for effective cloud operations

Architecting and engineering an enterprise-grade cloud foundation is a time consuming and multi-disciplinary undertaking. It requires deep expertise in security & regulatory requirements, network architecture, automation skills, operational support capabilities and knowledge of the latest best practices.

Digital Accelerators enable any enterprise to become as agile as a start-up by providing a “No-Ops” experience to developers

Even a well-built Cloud Foundation doesn't deliver value unless you are able to rapidly onboard business applications. The best way to accelerate developer adoption of this organization-wide cloud capability is by providing the autonomy and self-service that the developers crave for. Provide capabilities to make them highly productive by offering a straight-through processing experience.

Dev Tools

Fully integrated developer tools from ideation to production

Enable "you-build-it, you-own-it" culture

Dev Portal

Codified and pre-built application patterns and starter kits

Kickstart software projects and amplify developer productivity

Delivery Pipelines

Reference pipelines for continuous delivery of all application types and targets

Improve software quality and accelerate time to market

Deployment Targets

Full range of deployment targets from IaaS, CaaS, PaaS, to FaaS

Support both legacy and Cloud-native applications

The challenge in building these Digital Accelerators is compounded by the availability of a multitude of tools, wide variety of applications, and the different targets available for application deployments. It requires deep expertise in application design patterns, DevSecOps/SRE practices, software delivery pipelines, and knowledge of the latest best practices.

Enable your Enterprise IT to evolve from ITIL-based gatekeeping to being the proponent of the organizational change to DevSecOps excellence

Agility is one of the unmet promises of cloud for many organizations because they continue to operate in the traditional model even after migrating to cloud. Unlocking the true potential of cloud for your enterprise requires a next gen operating model driven by automation, self-service and decentralization.

Cloud Operating Model

Rewired organization minimizing silos, barriers, and handoffs and increased collaboration

Nimble and agile organization that is responsive to change

Process Reengineering for Cloud

Reengineered processes enabling automation, self-service, and decentralization

Developer autonomy resulting in faster time to market

Operations Playbooks

Ready-to-use guidance for operations teams that can effortlessly be used at scale to improve ops efficiency

Minimal effort to transition IT operations to support cloud

When it comes to Cloud adoption, the biggest challenge isn’t the technology - it's the people and processes that must change. For enterprises that don't take a strategic view to Cloud programs, Operations Readiness quite often becomes an after thought leading to delayed projects and unmet expectations. Just like any organizational change, it requires top-down planning and thoughtful execution.

Approach

BuiltRight

Operations Readiness

Delivered in 4 weeks, it’s your fastest path to value in Cloud.... guaranteed!

Assess

2 days

Collaborative and guided Discovery Workshop to assess the current state, understand business objectives, and to identify key drivers and requirements for target state

  • Review current state architecture and infrastructure code
  • Identify early adopters (applications to be migrated to cloud and/or to be built natively in Cloud)
  • Finalize the key foundational cloud capabilities for enterprise-wide use
  • Designate stakeholders for design & build reviews

Design

3 days

Target state Design Workshops to define a flexible and future proof architecture for each of the foundational capabilities aligned with Cloud Well-Architected Framework

  • Review and tailor out-of-the-box design blueprints that leverage industry best practices
  • Comprehensive policies and controls aligned to CIS, NIST CSF, PCI-DSS, HIPAA, etc.
  • Centralized mechanism to manage secrets, intelligently detect & respond to threats, identify vulnerabilities and secure end-points
  • Centrally managed just-in-time and just-enough role-based access control that seamlessly works across on-prem and public cloud
  • Cloud account framework that is aligned to the environment strategy of the applications, fulfills the financial accounting needs of the organization and minimizes the blast-radius
  • Comprehensive hybrid cloud network architecture that is highly resilient, secure and scalable
  • Operational capabilities that are fully automated (including image management, patch management, and private DNS)
  • Consistent enforcement of guardrails, controls, quotas, budgets, etc. across the cloud footprint to ensure compliance with IT policies and regulatory requirements
  • Centralized monitoring & logging, unified visualization, and correlation of different security & operational events
  • Centralized control of data protection from failures, security breaches, data leaks and disasters
  • 3rd party tool integrations

Build

5-10 days

Implement a fully operational and production-ready cloud foundation for enterprise-wide use using infrastructure as code integrating the right Cloud services and 3rd party products

  • Gather required configuration information
  • Deploy selected capabilities and features in a “cloud-lab” environment
  • Demo & walk-through of foundational capabilities to key stakeholders
  • Incorporate feedback and deploy to production cloud environment

Validate

5 days

Perform testing, validation, and production readiness certification in preparation for application onboarding

  • Validate the deployed cloud foundation is configured appropriately
  • Perform comprehensive end-to-end testing to certify all the capabilities deployed are production ready
  • Provide comprehensive documentation of built out cloud foundation (architecture, policies, and controls)
  • Train cloud engineering and operations teams
  • Sign-off and handover

Design

3 days

Target state design to define a nimble and agile operating model that is responsive to change and business needs

  • Review and customize the reference operating model design, RACI Matrix

Finalize

5 days

  • Target state operating model
